{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{distinguish|Nicholas D. Smith|Nicholas H. Smith}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Nick Smith''' |birth_date = 1972 |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[University of Sydney]] |main_interests = [[philosophy of language]], [[logic]] | thesis_title = Vagueness | thesis_url = https://search.proquest.com/docview/251106893 | thesis_year = 2001 | doctoral_advisor = [[Gideon Rosen]], [[John P. Burgess]] | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = degree-based theory of [[vagueness]] | spouse = | education = [[Princeton University]] (PhD), [[University of Sydney]] (BA) | alma_mater = |influences = |influenced = |awards = [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]] fellowship }}
'''Nicholas Jeremy Josef Smith''' (born 1972) is an Australian philosopher and Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Sydney]]. He is a fellow of the [[Australian Academy of the Humanities]] and a former President of the [[Australasian Association for Logic]]. Smith is known for his research on [[logics]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Paoli |first1=F. |title=Logic. The Laws of Truth |journal=[[History and Philosophy of Logic]] |date=27 March 2014 |volume=35 |issue=3 |pages=306–308 |doi=10.1080/01445340.2014.902243 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/01445340.2014.902243?journalCode=thpl20 |accessdate=15 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0144-5340}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cook |first1=Roy T. |title=Vagueness and Degrees of Truth - By Nicholas J. J. Smith |journal=Theoria |date=25 November 2010 |volume=76 |issue=4 |pages=380–384 |doi=10.1111/j.1755-2567.2010.01088.x |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/pdf/10.1111/j.1755-2567.2010.01088.x |accessdate=15 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0040-5825}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ripley |first1=David |title=Review of Vagueness and Degrees of Truth |journal=Analysis |date=2010 |volume=70 |issue=1 |pages=188–190 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/23315099?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>
