{{Expand Dutch|Concilie van Lhasa|date=December 2017}}
'''Samye Debate''', also called '''Council of Lhasa''', '''Council of Samye''', '''Debate of Samye''' or '''Great Debate''', was a two-year debate at Samye Temple hosted by [[Trisong Detsen]] between Indian Monastics from Nalanda and Chinese Moheyan from Tang Imperial Court between 792 and 794. [[Kamalasila|Kamalaśila]] was invited to represent [[Vajrayana]] while [[Moheyan]] represented the [[East Mountain Teaching]] of [[Chan Buddhism]].

