{{distinguish|text=the Australian and American television programs [[Sit Down, Shut Up (disambiguation)|Sit Down, Shut Up]]}}
{{Infobox book | name = Sit Down and Shut Up: Punk Rock Commentaries on Buddha, God, Truth, Sex, Death, & Dogen's Treasury of the Right Dharma Eye | image = Sit Down and Shut Up cover.jpg | caption = | author = [[Brad Warner]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | subject = [[Sōtō]] [[Zen|Zen Buddhism]], [[Dogen]] | publisher = [[New World Library]] | release_date = April 28, 2007 | media_type = Print | pages = 255 | isbn = 1-57731-559-6 | dewey= 294.3/85 22 | congress= BQ9288 .W377 2007 | oclc= 80020152 | preceded_by = [[Hardcore Zen]] | followed_by = }} '''''Sit Down and Shut Up: Punk Rock Commentaries on Buddha, God, Truth, Sex, Death, & Dogen's Treasury of the Right Dharma Eye''''' is a book written by [[Brad Warner]], an author and ordained [[Zen]] priest. The work serves as both an autobiography and an introduction to [[Dogen]]'s (道元) work ''[[Shōbōgenzō]]'' (正法眼蔵), (''Treasury of the Right Dharma Eye'').<ref name="genji">{{cite web |url=http://www.genjipress.com/2011/12/sit-down-and-shut-up-punk-rock.html |title=Books: Sit Down and Shut Up |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |publisher=Genji Press }}</ref>
==Reception==
The book received mixed reviews. ''[[Metro Silicon Valley|MetroActive]]'' stated "At times Warner comes off as pandering, with his cutesy pop-culture tangents and I-know-what-you're-thinking-right-now comments"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metroactive.com/metro/05.23.07/sit-down-and-shut-up-0721.html |title=Sit Down and Shut Up |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |quote= |publisher=[[Metro Silicon Valley|MetroActive]] }}</ref> while ''[[Buddhadharma: The Practitioner's Quarterly|Buddhadharma]]'' ultimately summed the book up with "Too much of an adolescent rant for most Zen readers and too much of a middle-aged strut down memory lane for most punk readers, ''Sit Down and Shut Up'' will likely get an enthusiastic reception only from the small group of readers who already identify as Zen punks."<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.thebuddhadharma.com/web-archive/2007/6/1/book-briefs.html |title=Book Briefs |author=Benjamin Bogin | journal =[[Buddhadharma: The Practitioner's Quarterly]] | issue =June 2007 |accessdate=May 17, 2012 }}</ref> ''[[Razorcake]]'', however, stated "Irreverent, cocksure, glib, and wise, this is one damn good book.".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.razorcake.org/punk-book-reviews/sit-down-and-shut-up-punk-rock-commentaries-on-buddha-god-truth-sex-death-by-brad-warner-1495-255-pgs |title=Sit Down and Shut Up |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |publisher=[[Razorcake]] }}</ref> The book received positive reviews from ''EnlightenNext'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.enlightennext.org/magazine/j38/reviews.asp |title=Natural Selection |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |publisher=EnlightenNext |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120803040747/http://www.enlightennext.org/magazine/j38/reviews.asp |archivedate=August 3, 2012 |df= }}</ref> ''[[Shambhala Sun]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shambhalasun.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=3136&Itemid=247 |title=Buddhism’s Young Turks |accessdate=May 17, 2012 |publisher=[[Shambhala Sun]] }}</ref> and ''Genji Press''.<ref name="genji"/>
Warner himself noted that he received some criticism of his handling of [[polyamory]] in the book.<ref name="reality">{{cite web|url=http://www.realitysandwich.com/zen_trickster|title=Zen Trickster: A Talk with Brad Warner|publisher=Reality Sandwich|accessdate=November 26, 2013}}</ref>
{{quote|A certain number of the polyamory people have gotten on my case about it. I don't hear from them directly, but I made the huge mistake of reading my Amazon customer reviews recently, and there was someone there who complained that I'd completely misconstrued the philosophy of polyamory -- so there's that contingent. Then you've got a certain number of the more traditional Buddhist crowd, who've never even heard of polyamory, who think I take a much too positive view of it. I feel that if I'm somewhere in the middle of those two sets of opinions, I must be doing something right.<ref name="reality"/>}}
== Publication data == * ''Sit Down and Shut Up: Punk Rock Commentaries on Buddha, God, Truth, Sex, Death, & Dogen's Treasury of the Right Dharma Eye'', Brad Warner, New World Library (May 2007), 255 pages, {{ISBN|1-57731-559-6}}
